translated: Liljedorff, Magnus, rural dean, Mantorp, b. 23/6/94 in Ingatorp, Jönköping. Son of L.G. 26 married to Anna Andersson. — Studied theology at Uppsala University, graduated in 1916, theology exam in 1919, theology candidate, practical theological examination and ordained in Linköping diocese in 1925. Pastor's assistant in Lofta in 1925, curate in Målilla the same year, vicar in Veta and Viby since 1928, rural dean in Vifolka and Valkebo deanery since 1939. Chairman of the church assembly, pastor's church assembly, elementary school board, Veta cemetery board, and Vifolka-Valkebo district of the Union of Active Priestly Personnel (ASP).
